          <h1>Mother Armenia, Gyumri</h1>
          <p>The Mother Armenia (Mayr Hayastan) monumental statue is a female personification of Armenia, located in the city of Gyumri. It resembles the monumental complex of Mother Armenia in the capital Yerevan. It was erected in 1975 on a hill west of Gyumri city. It was composed by sculptors Ara Sargsian and Yerem Vartanyan.[1] The architect is Rafik Yeghoyan.</p>
